properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued March 1 at 5:54AM AKST until March 1 at 7:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Visibility reduced to one
quarter mile or less at times. South to southwest winds
gusting 25 to 40 mph. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...Western Kenai Peninsula south of Clam Gulch.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 7 PM AKST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be very difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The worst conditions will be in the hills
north of Kachemak Bay. Conditions near sea level will not be
as bad as temperatures will start out in the mid to upper 30s.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 7 PM AKST THIS EVENING SOUTH OF CLAM GULCH
